<h1 id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-3.CoreFunctionality=E2=80=93Feed=
,InsightsandChat">3. Core Functionality =E2=80=93 Feed, Insights and Chat&n=
bsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d5ddc23f-6657-4f69-bf25-6e2=
90847881f" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 72.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 106.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 336.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 106.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 140.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Req No.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Priority&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Readiness and Plan</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"bb2323da-c150-407e-9de=
3-da2deee95184">Feeds will be shown based on the users interests. Our uniqu=
e feed algorithm will decide the relevance of the feeds shown. Users will b=
e able to jump to edit their interests and skills from the top of the Feed =
Page.&nbsp;</span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-1.1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed, Chat&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The search bar is auto-hidden when users scroll down. It will show again=
 when users scroll up&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>n/a. Not considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-1.2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed, Chat&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Search bar search at the top of Feed or Search, will search within the u=
ser feed or chat respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-1.3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed, Chat&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If user wants to search other feeds of interest, he may use =E2=80=9C&lt=
;interest&gt;:&lt;topic&gt;=E2=80=9D in the search bar. =E2=80=9C&lt;intere=
st&gt;:=E2=80=9D will assume a wild-card topic&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>n/a. Not considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed, Chat&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed will be scrollable down and up. Scrolling up will prompt the algori=
thm to pull in more feed. Scrolling down will continue to show less relevan=
t feed. (Past/seen feed is less relevant.) Less relevant feed will still be=
 based on user=E2=80=99s interests&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed Item&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Each Feed Item will have 3 parts. Item=E2=80=99s top part will show the =
a small-icon (e.g., ML in a circle) and the name of the interest (e.g. =E2=
=80=9C#machine-learning=E2=80=9D). There will also be additional interests =
(e.g. #fastai #python). Relevance will also be part of this feed item&nbsp;=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-4&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed Item&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Item=E2=80=99s middle part will show the feed items. Long press on a fee=
d item will highlight the whole feed item, which will allow copy-and-paste-=
elsewhere. More option will expand the feed button and show more informatio=
n (TBD)&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-5&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed Item&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Item=E2=80=99s bottom part will show following icons/actions: upvote, do=
wnvote, save and share.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-5.1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed Item&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Is highlighter needed? (No. For now) Do we render the feed-item with the=
 App? (Yes) Text size/font? (system default)&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>n/a. Not considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-5.2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed Item&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>tem=E2=80=99s bottom part will show following icons/actions: Note, micro=
phone icon</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-6&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed Item&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Upvotes and downvote will be used to show better feed to the user. User =
will be able see whether they upvoted or downvoted a feed (dark color vs. n=
eutral color). They can change their vote&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-7&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed Item&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Save will save the feed-item so that users can take a later action (e.g.=
, register for the course, read the paper etc.). Saved feeds will be availa=
ble on the Profile/Saved Feed page&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-8&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed Item&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Share will enable sharing the feed item with user=E2=80=99s contacts and=
 groups&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-9&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed items will be shown from the information available to the backend. =
The information sources will be the aggregator sites that we can scrub or d=
o api calls easily will be here (vs. searching more sites).&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-10&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Other feed sources will be the news/updates etc. from reddit, github OR =
news items, industry articles, blogs, papers etc.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-11&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Till the ML algorithms achieves the desired feed quality, the feed will =
be <u>curated</u> before fed to the users&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-12&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat Page will show users=E2=80=99 contacts who are also using Mentorlin=
k. (Note: there will be search bar at the top to search for users/groups)&n=
bsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6) =E2=80=93 in a roundabout way</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-13&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat Page will always show the =E2=80=9CShifu=E2=80=9D as the top contac=
t, clicking on which will enable the user to chat or talk to the ML backend=
 for any career questions&nbsp;</p>
<p>(Q: Do we need a proper name? Or one of the =E2=80=9CCoach=E2=80=9D, =E2=
=80=9CMentor=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9CShifu=E2=80=9D will do.)&nbsp;</p>
<p>*Note: UI/UX for mentors can be done within MVP. But this will not be po=
pulated&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-13.1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat functionality will add a voice-to-text translation in a later phase=
&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-14&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat Page will also show Broadcast List. Please see Broadcast list requi=
rements CF-22 for details&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>n/a. We will use group functionality instead.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-15&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat Page will also show Human Mentors of this user. Please see Human Me=
ntors requirements CF-23 for details. Human mentors will be pinned right af=
ter the Mentorlink =E2=80=9CMentor=E2=80=9D&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-16&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Clicking on another user, group, Mentorlink mentor or human mentors, wil=
l bring up a separate Chat Page with the relevant name at the top&nbsp;</p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-17&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/&lt;name&gt; Page&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This chat page will have a search bar at the top to search specific chat=
 on this chat page.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-18&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/&lt;name&gt; Page&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The named-chat page will show the individual chats in user=E2=80=99s dev=
ice (iMessage or google) chat format. E.g., Timestamp, left-side, right-sid=
e etc.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-19&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/&lt;name&gt; Page&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Individual chat items can be copied, upvoted, downvoted, saved, shared (=
just like the feed items)&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-20&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/&lt;name&gt; Page&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Individual chat items can be deleted from this user=E2=80=99s chat. (Not=
e: Users will not be able to delete the feed items)&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-21&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Feed Notification&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>There will be a gentle notification if there is an incoming chats as wel=
l as new feed=20
<del>(Note: There will be no notification for the new feed items)</del>&nbs=
p;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-22&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Broadcast list Page&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Users will be able to create broadcast lists and add their Mentorlink co=
ntacts in a group. Users will be able to delete these lists as well. Broadc=
ast List are local to a user only&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>n/a. We will use group functionality instead.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-22.1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Groups Page&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>There may be a group support in the future&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P4&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-23&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/&lt;Mentors&gt;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>=E2=80=9CShifu=E2=80=9D as well as Human mentors will have the same func=
tionality</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-23.1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/&lt;Mentors&gt;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Users will be able to send new mentorship requests to other users</p></t=
d>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-23.2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Human Mentors</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Users who have volunteered for new mentorships, will be able to accept o=
r deny mentees. Mentors can deny and it will show as an error. Standard err=
or will be =E2=80=9Cnot available for mentoring currently=E2=80=9D. New men=
torship requests and responses will be distinguished. If accepted, the resp=
onse will be =E2=80=9Cmentorlink success=E2=80=9D or some such thing.</p></=
td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-23.3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Human Mentors&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Mentors as well as mentees will have to go to the profile page to chat w=
ith mentors or mentees. Chat with a mentor will be distinguished (e.g. colo=
r) for the mentee as well as the mentor</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-24&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Human Mentors&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Users will be able to rate a mentor. ML mentor will be able to see its r=
ating by a user, but Human mentors will not be able to see their rating.&nb=
sp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-25&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Human Mentors&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Additional functionality requirements for the Human mentors will be TBD&=
nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-26&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Invite-a-Friend&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This link at the top will enable the user to send an invite link (txt or=
 email) using the user=E2=80=99s address book&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-27&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Chat/Camera&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>(Icon) Users will be able to upload pictures using the camera of their d=
evice&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>
<del>CF-28&nbsp;</del></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>
<del>Feed/Insights&nbsp;</del></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>
<del>(Icon) Users will be able to take a next step in their career (e.g., j=
obs, tasks etc.)&nbsp;</del></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>
<del>P2 (No longer applicable)</del></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>n/a. We are not targeting =E2=80=9Cphysiological=E2=80=9D need</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"446b30e6-b414-49e8-b16=
3-9b95cd2215c0">CF-29</span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Insights/User Engagement for an interest</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>(Icon) Insights page presents users with strategic mentorship. This page=
 will show user=E2=80=99s engagement for a particular interest (e.g. a dial=
). Engagement will be shown in terms of read feeds, upvoted feeds, shared f=
eeds, received (e.g. on one dial)</p>
<p>Alongwith the engagement dial, a time-series graph of user engagement fo=
r a particular interest is also shown</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"08dc56fb-e881-4d66-b4=
f1-bbd042a01ae4">1</span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-29.1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Insights/Goal Setting</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A user shall be able to set goals for engagement by clicking on the enga=
gement dial</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-30</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Insights/Career Journey</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Career Journey will show user his/her career journey since joining the m=
entorlink. An algorithm will arbitrarily choose a point to represent user=
=E2=80=99s rank with his/her peer group. Users will have an engagement scor=
e implies his/her movement in <u>the peer group</u> will be plotted/shown a=
s the career journey. Users engage by 1. sharing/receiving nudges 2. acting=
 upon feed items (voting, saving) 3. chatting with Shifu and other users 4.=
 Attending events 5. picking up and completing learning tasks etc.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-31</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Insights/Blind Spots - comparison with the peer-group</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Blind spots feature will be a comparison of user=E2=80=99s engagement wi=
th current interests, adjacent interests, top feed items compared to user=
=E2=80=99s peer group.</p>
<p>This can be shown as =E2=80=9Cshow peer=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Ccompare pe=
ers=E2=80=9D in the burger menu</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-32</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Insights/Blind Spots - trending topics</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Another category of interesting stuff is trending feed items and trendin=
g new topics within user=E2=80=99s peer group or senior group. This sub-fea=
ture is purely meant to be show latest trends and has a suggested time-wind=
ow of 1 day</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-33</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Career Wallet</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Users will be able to store all their activities in their career wallets=
. e.g.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Courses taken, transcripts</p></li>
<li>
<p>Conferences, events attended</p></li>
<li>
<p>Temporary assignments or internships*</p></li>
<li>
<p>Human mentor recommendations</p></li>
<li>
<p>Human mentor schedule books and workbooks</p></li>
</ol>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"xsv7sk2ag2">{*This will be part of the feed along =
with the trivia, code writing tests etc.? }</span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-34</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Career Wallet/Job Help</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"53a4c62b-5b55-4fbd-b2a=
4-916693626d2c">This sub-feature will show prospects of job role outlook, i=
ndustry outlook etc.</span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>CF-35</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Feed/Settings</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Users may be able to choose their feed settings (interest vs user-profil=
e) under the settings</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-4.FailureHandling">4. Failure Ha=
ndling&nbsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"8ae25038-edc4-493a-b683-d41=
fef65def2" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 71.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 128.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 309.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 112.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 140.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Req No.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Priority&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Readiness and Plan</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UI/UX, Front End&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UI/UX Crash will send a crash report to the backend. UI/UX will restart =
gracefully by getting the last saved context from the backend&nbsp;</p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To implement a graceful restart Front End will continue to check point t=
he user=E2=80=99s state after every =E2=80=9Cn=E2=80=9D events. (N=3D3?)&nb=
sp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Analytics data will be saved and streamed based on the choice of the Ana=
lytics Bus&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-4&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Idle State&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Idle timeout of 30 mins, will essentially be treated as a new login and =
a fresh feed will be shown w/o any context. Hence the app must constantly h=
ave an idle timeout running&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-6&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Backend&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All backend services should be able to handle failures gracefully. They =
should be able to start from the last checkpointed state. Every service (pu=
re backend, ML, Analytics) will have its own checkpointing logic&nbsp;</p><=
/td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-7&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Backend External Services&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Backend external services will have a stricter failure handling requirem=
ent. 3<sup>rd</sup> Party API services cost money and we require the API se=
rvices not to make unnecessary API calls&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-8&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>External Failures&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Backend will be hosted on the cloud. Occasionally there will be cloud ve=
ndor=E2=80=99s infra or other 3<sup>rd</sup> party software failures. Backe=
nd should be able to handle at least 2 cascaded failures&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-9&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Frontend will not know whether a backend has crashed or it is slow. Fron=
tend will retry to connect with the backend with an exponential back-off&nb=
sp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Not sure</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>FH-10&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Database&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>User data, analytics data, monetization data will never be lost. There w=
ill be multiple layers of protection to make this happen&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-5.Upgrade,Downgrade,SoftwareVers=
ioning">5. Upgrade, Downgrade, Software Versioning&nbsp;&nbsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"b9f3327b-7a4a-476b-9c6a-00b=
47dc48d0e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 99.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 98.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 330.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 93.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 140.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Req No.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Priority&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Readiness and Plan</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Upgrade&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Upgrades are pushed out for every stable release of the product. Upgrade=
 procedure will allow only two <u>major</u> versions (current version and n=
ew version) of the product. Older devices or users who avoid the upgrade wi=
ll not be able to connect to the backend and will be asked to get a newer d=
evices or upgrade. Minor versions are used for bug-fixing releases. Please =
refer to UD-9 for versioning details.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1 (6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>App upgrade procedure is rolled out in an expanding circle fashion. A sm=
all set of users get the newest version. Once they are able to operate in a=
 stable fashion, the next expanding circle of users is upgraded. (Dashboard=
 like =E2=80=9Clooker=E2=80=9D may be used to roll out the upgrades.)&nbsp;=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If there is a stability issue in the n-th circle, the upgrade procedure =
will stop and all the users in that circle are rolled back to the previous =
version of the software. No earlier versions allowed by UD-1&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>We will keep the working devices on the version, instead of doin=
g a rollback the entire circle.</strong> <u>Pros/cons:</u> Rolling back the=
 full circle is =E2=80=9Ctransaction=E2=80=9D model and may be simpler to i=
mplement. Keeping working device on the version helps with the debug/issue-=
finding. Circle-roll-back model may run into convergence issues, which keep=
-the-version model avoids&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-4&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Any newer versions of the software are released only after the latest ve=
rsion is pushed successfully to all the users&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-5&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Post UD-3 scenario (i.e., bug fixing of new version of the software), th=
e expanding circle is restarts and starts from the same circle again.&nbsp;=
</p>
<p><strong>Smaller circle can stay with earlier minor aka pre-bugfix versio=
n, instead of getting upgraded&nbsp; with the next minor version.</strong>&=
nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-6&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Database schema, app backend, modified or new services will handle the u=
pgrade/downgrade scheme as described in earlier requirements. (Clarificatio=
n: App frontend will depend on the device OS upgrade scheme.)&nbsp;</p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-7&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Downgrade&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>There is no downgrade of software allowed except in the <a class=3D"exte=
rnal-link" href=3D"http://mentorlink.ai" rel=3D"nofollow">mentorlink.ai</a>=
 labs&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Not sure. Does Testflight support this?</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-8&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Upgrade/Downgrade&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Multiple versions of software will be available for development and test=
ing in <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://mentorlink.ai" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">mentorlink.ai</a> labs&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Not sure. Does Testflight support this?</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UD-9&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Software Versioning&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Major versions are meant for major functionality delivery. Minor version=
s are used for bug-fixing versions. Sub-minor versions may be used for A/B =
testing. Please refer to UF-1 for details for the details on the A/B testin=
g.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-6.DataCollection,AnalyticsandLog=
ging">6. Data Collection, Analytics and Logging&nbsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"dedd8919-ddac-45e1-b250-297=
b0e7ce974" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 82.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 121.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 324.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 93.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 140.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Req No.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Priority&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Readiness and Plan</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>DC-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>App Data Collection&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>There will be a fine-grained telemetry available from the App. Every cli=
ck, button press (upvotes, downvotes, shared, saved, etc.) <u>within</u> th=
e app will be collected.&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>EULA will be shown to user at the time of sign-on. Check complia=
nce on the data collection.</strong>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>DC-2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>App will collect user data with user permissions (e.g., contacts, email =
addresses (if google sign-up) etc. &nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>EULA will be shown to user at the time of sign-on. Check complia=
nce on the data collection.</strong>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>DC-3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>App will collect app contextual data (e.g., app placement on the device,=
 app swipe/open/close data, notification settings, other apps on the phone =
etc.) in compliance with the App Store policies and in compliance with GDPR=
, CCPA (California)&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>
<del>DC-4</del>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>
<del>Backend 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Data Collection</del>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>
<del>Please refer to CF-9 and CF-10</del>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>
<del>P1</del>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>n/a</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>DC-5&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Backend Services&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All the services will maintain fine grain stats about the messages and c=
alls for every code path within the service&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>DC-6&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All the services will maintain fine grain stats about the per user workf=
low data (if a cookie is available). Per user workflow data may be used to =
optimize users=E2=80=99 overall experience&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>DC-7&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Logging&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Front End as well as Backend services will implement a robust logging me=
chanism. Logging levels will be Error (services encountered an unrecoverabl=
e error and needs to restart), Warning (services encountered a recoverable =
error), Information (services want to inform of an event for later analysis=
), Trace (services are debugging)&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>(TODO: two different types of logging?)</strong>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-7.UserFeedback">7. User Feedback=
&nbsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d0bf98a8-bb20-445c-bedb-4f5=
8b68923cf" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 83.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 113.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 323.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 101.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 140.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Req No.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Priority&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Readiness and Plan</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UF-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A/B Testing&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All major functionality changes will undergo A/B testing. (Note: one met=
hod could be to use different sub-minor version for different services)&nbs=
p;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UF-2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No more than one A/B testing is allowed per service at any time&nbsp;</p=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>10.2.1 and 10.2.2 --&gt; two versions for A/B testing with recommendatio=
n algo A vs B&nbsp;</p>
<p>10.2.10 and 10.2.11 --&gt; two versions for A/B testing for chat algo A =
vs B&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-8.API">8. API&nbsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"dc1ebc6c-8e55-4590-a7f2-324=
94d651a97" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 87.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 83.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 352.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 98.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 140.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Req No.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Priority&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Readiness and Plan</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>API-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>API&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All services except external services may use the API with the optimal p=
erformance. E.g., protobuf. The choice for this is left to the design.&nbsp=
;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>API-2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Each service is required to publish an API to get, set, add-new, delete =
APIs for all the objects in its data model. Services may control the access=
 using authentication and permissions. The choice for this is left to the d=
esign.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>API-3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3<sup>rd</sup> Party non-developer API&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://Mentorlink.ai" rel=3D"nofollow=
">Mentorlink.ai</a> provided 3<sup>rd</sup> Party non-developer APIs will h=
ave human-readable API interface. The schemas for these APIs will be comply=
 to the Upgrade/Downgrade requirements. These will be business APIs and wil=
l not be available w/o a business relationship&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>API-4&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3<sup>rd</sup> Party Developer APIs&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://Mentorlink.ai" rel=3D"nofollow=
">Mentorlink.ai</a> developer APIs will also comply to API-4. We do not hav=
e control over other vendors=E2=80=99 developer APIs. Developer APIs may be=
 used by 3<sup>rd</sup> party developers to get limited data&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-9.ScaleandPerformance">9. Scale =
and Performance&nbsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"845ef66f-660e-4e8e-bbca-179=
76560b5b9" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 96.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 130.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 302.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 92.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 140.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Req No.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Priority&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Readiness and Plan</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SP-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Scale&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Number of users will be in the range of 1000-5000 in the MVP version&nbs=
p;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SP-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The backend is required to scale to ~1000 QPS per service in the MVP ver=
sion&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SP-3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Performance&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Each user should be able to operate the app w/o any noticeable response =
delay (max 5 ms)&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SP-4&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Cloud&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Backend services will be hosted on a cloud.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SP-4&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Horizontal Scaling&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Backend services will scale horizontally and handle additional user load=
 appropriately&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3.1(6)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-10.AuthenticationandSecurity">10=
. Authentication and Security&nbsp;&nbsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"af3caa31-43e8-4232-9221-c44=
db54539e4" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 81.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 93.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 354.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 92.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 140.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Req No.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Description&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Priority&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Readiness and Plan</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>AS-1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Admin&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>There would be at least 3 kinds of Admins in the system. Data Admin will=
 have the responsibility for the Data integrity and accessibility. Infra Ad=
min will have the responsibility to make sure the compute and network integ=
rity and accessibility.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>AS-2&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Data Admin will be able to have access to all the APIs of all the servic=
es&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>AS-3&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All data residing within each service will be available for read, write,=
 modify to the Data Admin&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>AS-4&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Authentication&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All admins must use 2-factor authentication for any access to the data (=
or infra)&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>AS-5&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Security&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Critical user data (name, role) that can be used to access individual us=
ers will be stored encrypted&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P1&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>To be considered for Mentorlink Next</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 style=3D"text-align: center;" id=3D"MentorlinkAppProductRequirements-Ap=
pendixA"><em>Appendix A</em>&nbsp;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-w=
rapper"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" loading=3D"la=
zy" src=3D"ce5835278545edc0121fc4da72dc812f4d0637c67f183e15e05e8be1d37f256c=
" data-image-src=3D"https://mentorlink.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachme=
